doc_summary_long: Privately held ride-hailing company Uber Technologies Inc lost more than $800 million in the third quarter, Bloomberg reported on Monday. In the previous quarter the company's loss significantly exceeded $800 million, including its Chinese operations, Bloomberg said. Uber generated about $1.7 billion in net revenue in the third quarter, up from $1.1 billion in the previous quarter, Bloomberg reported.
doc_summary_short: Privately held ride-hailing company Uber Technologies Inc lost more than $800 million in the third quarter, Bloomberg reported on Monday.
doc_title: Uber lost more than $800 million in third quarter 2016: Bloomberg
